body:
I always loved Cowboys in past and present culture, back then they promoted a sort of sauntered way of living, and now it represents a time long gone. McCree was always my favorite character from Overwatch (Not just because he&#039;s a cowboy lol,) but because I was always intrigued by his story, his morals, and his character design. I understand that people think that in games like League and Overwatch, cowboys are cliche and very niche, and I gotta say it, they are. But they always hold near and dear to people&#039;s hearts, and also how most portrayals of cowboys are one of the most 3-dimensional archetypes in fiction. I never cared for Graves so much, because I felt that the idea of him was out of place in League, but not because of him as a cowboy, but because his connections to the lore of league as a whole doesn&#039;t feel like it&#039;s on the same plane. I may just be rambling, but I hope Riot does more with Graves to develop him in the game more, because yippy caye yay, are cowboys awesome. 

So now I leave you with one of my favorite quotes of all time,

See you, Space Cowboy :)  {{champion:104}}
